- "weight of the intellectual baggage" refers to the average file size (file_size column); 
- "active file" refers to a file where is_active equals 1; 
- "dependencies" refers to entries in the dependencies table where the parent_id matches the file_id.

- File dependencies are used to track how files relate to each other in the project structure; 
- Average file ratings are calculated based on user feedback and are used to measure file quality; 
- The latest access date indicates when a file was last opened or modified; 
- Project summaries are used to evaluate project performance based on file metrics.
